						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Chōḻa, Rajakesarivarman, Year 14 = c. 10th Century.</hi></p>						

						<p>This records a gift of 15 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold by <hi rend="italic">kāseṭṭānkal</hi> for burning a lamp in the temple of Tiruchchankōṭṭu-Āḻvār by Muri-Amudanār, the wife of Iḷangōnaḍikaḷ. The gift was left in charge of the body called Panniraṇḍu-nāṭṭu-perumakkaḷ.</p>						

						<p>[Published in <hi rend="italic">SII</hi> Vol. XIII, No. 242.]</p>						

